#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Sacittavagga"
msgstr "6. Your Own Mind"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Dutiyasaññāsutta"
msgstr "57. Perceptions (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.106"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.57:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Dasayimā, bhikkhave, saññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti mahānisaṃsā "
"amatogadhā amatapariyosānā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, these ten perceptions, when developed and cultivated, are very "
"fruitful and beneficial. They culminate in the deathless and end with the "
"deathless."

msgctxt "an10.57:1.2"
msgid "Katamā dasa?"
msgstr "What ten?"

#. VAR: puḷavakasaññā → pulavakasaññā (bj) | puḷuvakasaññā (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an10.57:1.3"
msgid ""
"Aniccasaññā, anattasaññā, maraṇasaññā, āhāre paṭikūlasaññā, sabbaloke "
"anabhiratasaññā, aṭṭhikasaññā, puḷavakasaññā, vinīlakasaññā, "
"vicchiddakasaññā, uddhumātakasaññā—"
msgstr ""
"The perceptions of impermanence, not-self, death, repulsiveness of food, "
"dissatisfaction with the whole world, a skeleton, a worm-infested corpse, a "
"livid corpse, a split open corpse, and a bloated corpse."

msgctxt "an10.57:1.4"
msgid ""
"imā kho, bhikkhave, dasa saññā bhāvitā bahulīkatā mahapphalā honti "
"mahānisaṃsā amatogadhā amatapariyosānā”ti."
msgstr ""
"These ten perceptions, when developed and cultivated, are very fruitful and "
"beneficial. They culminate in the deathless and end with the deathless.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.57:1.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
